    "system": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p>When you attack while &amp;Reference[invisible] in a way that would end invisibility, such as with your @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.7Gnq3qfLzpIuRs0U]{Meld in Shadows} ability or with the <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.vWQiuirTFxetH3lm]{Invisibility}</em> spell, you remain invisible until the end of the current turn, even if you would normally become visible after attacking. If you attack while using @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.Z1WevTWQhrRwwyp8]{Hijack Shadow}, you remain in your target's shadow until the end of the current turn.</p><p></p><p><strong>Note: This ability is not automated, so your invisibility condition may end when it should not.</strong></p>",
